gomodel:SYNGO_4742  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3a: \"Hippocampal neurons were preloaded with the FRET substrate and treated with BDNF (50 ng/ml) for 10 min or EGF (20 ng/ml) for 2 min. They were then fixed, stained with phalloidin-Alexa Fluor594, and processed for confocal microscopy. Decrease in FRET signal (increased fluorescence) was observed in dendrites as well as in dendritic spine-like structures labeled with phalloidin-Alexa Fluor594 (arrows)\". Experimental description: M&M: \"Whole cerebral neocortex of embryonic day 18-19 rats (Sprague Dawley) or hippocampi of embryonic day 18 mice (BALB/c) were digested with trypsin before mechanical dissociation and plating\"\n\nIn vitro analysis was performed using purified rat m-calpain (0.5 μm; Calbiochem), the FRET substrate (100 μm), and CaCl2 (5 mm) in 50 μl calpain buffer (in mm: 50 Tris, 150 NaCl, and 1 EDTA, pH 7.5) inside a 10 mm UV quartz cuvette at room temperature and using a HORIBA Jobin Yvon FluoroMax-3 spectrofluorometer." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-08-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4742" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

